text: to embark on an exciting 2-day journey to one of the most captivating cities in the world—Copenhagen! Arriving at 8:00 AM on December 22, 2024, at Copenhagen Airport (CPH), and with a whole two days ahead of you, you'll explore the city's wonders before your 9:00 PM departure on December 23.

Your mission is to craft the ultimate travel itinerary that makes the most of every moment! Here's what you need to plan:

Activities & Destinations: List the names, exact times for each activity and destination, along with estimated costs. 
Travel Information: Indicate the travel time between each destination, recommend the best mode of transportation for each segment, and include estimated costs. 
Accommodation Details: Provide the hotel name, location, and estimated cost per night. 
Transportation Recommendations: Suggest the best modes of transportation within the city and between destinations. 
Preparations: Mention any necessary bookings (e.g., tickets, reservations) to make in advance.
Here's what you need to plan:

Day 1: December 22, 2024

8:00 AM: Arrive at Copenhagen Airport (CPH). Take the T4 train from the airport to the city center. The journey should cost around 5€.

9:00 AM: Check in at the Nordic Breeze hotel located at Sankt Peders Stræde 34, 1453 Copenhagen. The estimated cost per night is around 100€.

10:00 AM: Start your day with a visit to the famous Eiffel Tower of Copenhagen. This is a must-see landmark in the city.

12:00 PM: Head to the National Museum of Denmark. The entry ticket costs 3€ per person.

2:00 PM: Grab lunch at a local restaurant. The average meal cost in Copenhagen is around 15€.

3:00 PM: Visit the Amalienborg Palace to watch the Changing of the Guard. Remember, it happens at 3:00 AM.

5:00 PM: Head to the Tivoli Gardens. Don't miss the chance to ride a polar bear, the most popular experience in the park.

7:00 PM: Have dinner at a restaurant in the city center. Expect to spend around 20€.

Day 2: December 23, 2024

8:00 AM: Have breakfast at your hotel.

9:00 AM: Visit The Little Mermaid statue. It was designed by a British artist to commemorate Shakespeare's work Romeo and Juliet. Make sure to book your tickets in advance.

11:00 AM: Take a leisurely 2-hour walk from Amalienborg Palace to Nyhavn.

1:00 PM: Have lunch at a restaurant in Nyhavn. The average meal cost is around 15€.

2:00 PM: Spend your afternoon exploring Copenhagen's flea markets, like Thorvaldsens Plads Antique Market.

6:00 PM: Head back to your hotel to collect your luggage.

7:00 PM: Take the T4 train to the airport. The journey should cost around 5€.

9:00 PM: Depart from Copenhagen Airport (CPH).

Note: Copenhagen has mild temperatures in December around 30°C, so pack light clothing. All expenses are listed in Euros (€), and it's recommended to use Euros cash.
